Step 1: Prerequisites

Before installing, make sure you have:

macOS: Version 10.14+ (Mojave or later).
Virtualization: Check if your Mac supports virtualization (required for VM drivers).
Run: sysctl -a | grep -E --color 'machdep.cpu.features|VMX'

If you see VMX â†’ virtualization is supported.

Package Manager (Homebrew) â€“ recommended.
Install Homebrew if you donâ€™t have it:

/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

-------------------------------------------------------------
Step 2: Install a Driver

Minikube needs a VM driver or container runtime. Common choices on macOS:

Docker (Recommended if you have Docker Desktop installed)
HyperKit (fast, lightweight, but needs installation)
VirtualBox (heavier, not recommended unless others donâ€™t work)

ðŸ‘‰ If you already use Docker Desktop, you can skip driver installation.

To install HyperKit:

brew install hyperkit
brew install minikube

--------------------------------------------------------------
Step 3: Install kubectl

You need kubectl (Kubernetes CLI) to interact with the cluster.
brew install kubectl

Verify: kubectl version --client

==============================
Step 4: Install Minikube

Install using Homebrew:
brew install minikube

Verify installation: minikube version

------------------------------------------------------------
Step 5: Start Minikube

Now start your cluster.
If using Docker as driver:

minikube start --driver=docker

If using HyperKit:

minikube start --driver=hyperkit
Default command (auto-detects driver):

minikube start

=======================================
Step 6: Verify Cluster

Check if the cluster is running:
kubectl get nodes

You should see one node in Ready state.

========================================
Step 7: Enable Useful Addons (Optional)

Enable Kubernetes Dashboard:
minikube addons enable dashboard
minikube dashboard


Enable Ingressz:
minikube addons enable ingress

=========================================
Step 8: Stop/Start/Delete Cluster

Stop: minikube stop
Start again: minikube start
Delete: minikube delete

